<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,370,676]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Barcode analysis revealed that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Herrick)" baseAuthorityName="Herrick" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[519,1013,370,396]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Diaptomidae" genus="Leptodiaptomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Calanoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novamexicanus">
<emphasis box="[519,896,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Leptodiaptomus novamexicanus</emphasis>
(Herrick)
</taxonomicName>
was a group of species, reinforcing earlier conclusions based on morphology. Osorio-Tafall (1942) was the first to make this suggestion, describing 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Osorio-Tafall" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[198,480,450,475]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Diaptomidae" genus="Leptodiaptomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Calanoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garciai">
<emphasis box="[198,480,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Leptodiaptomus garciai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the unique saline Alchichica Crater Lake. Our barcoding results, together with data on ecophysiology, morphology and breeding studies (Montiel et al, 2008) support recognition of this species as a valid taxon, in opposition to the synonymy proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson" box="[959,1132,530,556]" firstAuthor="Wilson" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="738 - 794" refId="ref11994" refString="Wilson, M. S. (1959) Free - living Copepoda Calanoida. In: Ward and Whipple's Freshwater Biology, 2 nd ed., W. T. Edmonson, ed., Wiley, New York, pp. 738 - 794." type="book chapter" year="1959">Wilson (1959)</bibRefCitation>
. Moreover, in the State of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,244,570,596]" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, we found two related, but definitely different forms of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herrick" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[922,1136,570,595]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Diaptomidae" genus="Leptodiaptomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Calanoida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novamexicanus">
<emphasis box="[922,1136,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">L. novamexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Again it is necessary to compare specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[498,548,610,636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
locality (a reservoir in Albuquerque, New 
<collectingRegion box="[1057,1148,610,636]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Mexico</collectingRegion>
) with those found in the central plateau of 
<collectingCountry box="[361,454,650,676]" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
